%spark
// Load and parse the data
tmp = sc.textFile("oci://bdcsbk@smcloud10/"+Directory+"/Sample_Customer_History.csv")
val t_header = tmp.first() //extract header
val t_data = tmp.filter(row => row != t_header)
val t_userProducts = t_data.map(_.split(",") match { case Array(user, item, _, _, _, _, _, _) =>
  (user.toInt, item.toInt)
})

val t_predictions =
  model.predict(t_userProducts).map { case Rating(user, product, rate) =>
    (user, product, rate)
  }
  
t_predictions.collect().foreach(println)

%spark
// convert to proper dataframe and write to csv
import java.io._
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._

val file = "oci://bdcsbk@smcloud10/"+Directory+"/output"

t_predictions.toDF().createOrReplaceTempView("unsorted")
spark.sql("select sample_history_temp.*, unsorted._3 from sample_history_temp join unsorted on (sample_history_temp.Customer_ID=unsorted._1 and sample_history_temp.Product_ID=unsorted._2)").createOrReplaceTempView("sorted")
spark.catalog.dropTempView("unsorted")
spark.sql("select Customer_ID, max(_3) as _3 from sorted group by Customer_ID").createOrReplaceTempView("grouped")
val output = spark.sql("select sorted.Customer_ID, sorted.Product_ID, sorted.Product_Name, sorted.Customer_Email, sorted._3 as Scores from grouped inner join sorted on (grouped.Customer_ID = sorted.Customer_ID and grouped._3 = sorted._3)")

output.coalesce(1).write.option("header","true").csv(file)

%sh
# fix csv name
BASE=$(grep bdcsce_default_objectstore_url /etc/bdcsce/conf/datasources.properties |cut -d= -f2 |sed 's%/*$%%')

hdfs dfs -mv $BASE/supermart/output/*.csv $BASE/supermart/output.csv
hdfs dfs -rm $BASE/supermart/output/*
hdfs dfs -rmr $BASE/supermart/output
